2009-07-01  ZHANG Linbo  <zlb@pc111>

	* src/utils.c 1.300: fix memory leak in phgRealloc__().

	* src/hierarchical-basis.c 1.103, src/hp.c 1.87, src/intergrid.c 1.31, src/map.c 1.122, src/matvec.c 1.221, src/medit.c 1.65, src/option.c 1.117, src/periodic.c 1.33, src/phg-mpi.c 1.38, src/quad.c 1.169, src/solver-pardiso.c 1.12, src/utils.c 1.299, include/utils.h 1.64, src/distribute.c 1.156, src/dof.c 1.268:
	1. implement phgRealloc__() which calls malloc+memcpy if realloc fails.
	2. define macro phgRealloc_(ptr, size, oldsize) (it calls phgRealloc by default,
	   and can be changed to call phgRealloc__, see note below)
	Note: the realloc() function randomly fails on DeepComp7000 when using MVAPICH2
	with more than 64 processes, and phgRealloc__() provides a workaround for this
	problem (simply change the macro phgRealloc_ to call phgRealloc__ instead of
	phgRealloc).

