2008-12-20  liuhui  <liuhui@pc111>

	* src/partition-sfc.c 1.46: add: enlarge bounding box  function
	add: add function that doesn't keep domain ratio
	     ext[0] = 1. /ext[0];
	     ext[1] = 1. /ext[1];
	     ext[2] = 1. /ext[2];

	     experiments show that partitioning quality is worse when
	     domain has large domain ratio!!!

	add: printf more information when verbosity > 0
	     partitioning information and remapping information

