2008-11-22  ZHANG Linbo  <zlb@pc111>

	* src/solver-pardiso.c 1.5: add "-pardiso_refine" option

	* configure 1.190: update

	* configure.in 1.185:
	add -lpthread with MKL (needed when gcc, not mpicc, is used)

	* src/solver-pardiso.c 1.4:
	add optional code for tracing PARDISO calls.

	* src/solver-pardiso.c 1.3: change type of 'pt' and 'iparm' to 'int'

	* src/solver-pardiso.c 1.2:
	use 'size_t' instead of 'void *' for some PARDISO arrays.

	* configure 1.189: update

	* configure.in 1.184:
	Change order of checking such that BLAS/LAPACK are search in the order:

	    PETSc => PARDISO (BLAS only) => user => if not found then MKL and others

	The libs found later take precedence.
	Thus user supplied BLAS/LAPACK will always be effective.

	* configure 1.188, make-dist.list 1.18, src/Makefile.dep 1.54: update

	* configure.in 1.183, include/config.h.in 1.29, include/solver.h 1.106, src/Makefile 1.51, src/solver-pardiso.c 1.1, src/solver.c 1.288:
	implement (MKL) PARDISO solver interface.

	* src/utils.c 1.287:
	initialize OMP_NUM_THREADS to 1 if it's undefined (single thread by default).

	* src/solver-mumps.c 1.62: change default symmetry to 'spd'

