2006-12-19  ZHANG Linbo  <zlb@pc111>

	* src/dof-utils.c 1.22:
	bugfix in phgDofCopy_: If src DOF is discontinuous, the values stored in dest
	are multiplied by corresponding weight. However, the InitFunc of dest may
	use previously computed data in dest (e.g., with HFEB2, when calling InitFunc
	on a face, data on the edges of the face are used), thus the results in this
	case might be wrong (a typical example is DG2 ==> HFEB2). The fix consists
	of storing correct data in dest, and the weighted data in 'buffer'

	* test/dof_test.c 1.31, examples/maxwell.c 1.46: update

	* src/hfeb.c 1.23:
	cleanup (to be investigated: incorrect result for DG2 ==> HFEB2 in dof_test.c)

	* test/dof_test.c 1.30: update

	* src/hfeb.c 1.22:
	bugfixes and reimplementation of InitFunc of HFEB2 using L2 projection.

	* src/dof-utils.c 1.21: update

	* include/dof.h 1.58:
	better use of temperary variables in phgGet{Edge,Face}Vertices

	* src/hfeb.c 1.21, doc/chap4.tex 1.45, src/solver.c 1.152, test/dof_test.c 1.29:
	update

