2006-12-15  ZHANG Linbo  <zlb@pc111>

	* test/.cvsignore 1.16, examples/.cvsignore 1.11, doc/chapa.tex 1.117:
	update

	* test/dof_testm.c 1.1: *** empty log message ***

	* src/dof-utils.c 1.12:
	remove WARN_UNTESTED macros from tested cases in phgDofMM

	* include/matvec.h 1.20, src/dof-utils.c 1.11, src/eigen-blopex.c 1.14, src/eigen-jdbsym.c 1.25, src/eigen-primme.c 1.14, src/matvec.c 1.27, src/solver-pcg.c 1.38:
	rename MAT_OP_NONE to MAT_OP_N, MAT_TRANS to MAT_OP_T

	* src/dof-utils.c 1.10:
	set userfunc to DofNoAction in phgDofAXPBY() and phgDofMM()

	* doc/chap4.tex 1.43, include/dof.h 1.56, include/utils.h 1.42, src/dof-utils.c 1.9, src/dof.c 1.119, src/hierarchical-basis.c 1.14, src/nedelec.c 1.31:
	fix a critical bug: phgDofSetDataByFunction_ does not step over all element
	basis functions in order, thus functions using a dummy USER_FUNC_LAMBDA
	function which uses pre-evaluated basis function values at nodal points,
	such as phgDofGradient and phgDofDivergence, do not work (except with
	the DGn elements).

	The fix consists of adding a new argument 'bno' to USER_FUNC_LAMBDA, which
	is the index of the local basis function (or local index of the point).

	* src/dof-utils.c 1.8: finish implementation of phgDofMM (untested)

	* test/dof_test.c 1.26, test/dof_test1.c 1.51, test/dof_test4.c 1.6:
	update

	* doc/chapa.tex 1.116, include/dof.h 1.55, src/dof.c 1.118:
	new function phgDofSetDataByValuesV

