2006-03-26  ZHANG Linbo  <zlb@pc111>

	* doc/chap1.tex 1.10, doc/chap3.tex 1.20, doc/chap4.tex 1.13, doc/chapa.tex 1.44, doc/defs.sty 1.19, examples/poisson.c 1.206, examples/simplest.c 1.45, include/dof.h 1.10, include/phg.h 1.13, include/utils.h 1.13, phg_tcl/phg_tcl.c 1.5, src/albert.c 1.5, src/distribute.c 1.39, src/dof.c 1.25, src/geom.c 1.4, src/lagrange.c 1.3, src/medit.c 1.12, src/opendx.c 1.5, src/phg-mpi.c 1.16, src/solver.c 1.61, src/utils.c 1.60, src/vtk.c 1.4, test/coarsen_test.c 1.41, test/dof_test.c 1.11, test/phg_test.c 1.15:
	Massive changes for facilitating updating indices in the parallel coarsening
	algorithm (files before these changes have been tagged with 'v0_4_1'):

	1. g->nedge/g->nface/g->nelem are the numbers of edge/face/elem indices
	   referenced in the whole tree (i.e., size of g->L2Gmap_xxx). g->nleaf
	   still means the number of leaf elements.
	   Now all 4 types of DOF data, not just VERTEX data, may have holes
	   (UNREFERENCED entries).

	2. Valid local indices are stored on all elements in the tree, not just
	   leaf elements.

	3. Changes in macro/function names:
		xxxxVolume ==> xxxxElement,
		g->L2Gmap ==> g->L2Gmap_elem,
		phgDofGetBoundaryType ==> phgDofGetElementBoundaryType,
		phgDofGetCoordinates ==> phgDofGetElementCoordinates

2006-03-26  tcui  <tcui@pc111>

	* examples/time-harmonic-e1.c 1.22:
	implement phgQuadFuncDotBas() for rhs computing

